name: Extortion in the second degree
text:
(1)  A person commits the offense of extortion in the second degree if the person commits extortion:



	(a)	Of property or services the value of which exceeds $50 during any twelve-month period; or
	(b)	As set forth in section 707-764(2).



	(2)  Extortion in the second degree is a class C felony. [L 1979, c 106, pt of §1; am L 1993, c 28, §1]
Case Notes
  Terroristic threatening in the second degree is not a lesser included offense of attempted extortion in the second degree.  70 H. 456, 776 P.2d 392.
